Saturday, I'm planning to try again. The weather looks a bit bad, but it's only Monday.
It seems that the challenge in this regard has already begun. Due to the FAA's stance on certain drugs, I may have difficulty obtaining a medical certificate.
This is not impossible, but it will take a lot of time and require a lot of extra work.
Although this is a bit disappointing, it's just another problem that needs to be solved, and it looks like it can be solved. However, it will require a lot of time and money.
If you want to know what I'm going to face next:
FAA does not like ADHD. If you are taking medication for ADHD, you definitely won't pass the medical examination.
